metadata.name: Specter of Fears #26
metadata.description:
In the dreamlike landscape of our minds, the specter of fears is like a wraith, ever-present and ethereal. It whispers in our ear, reminding us of all the things we dare not face. It is a shadow that falls across our hearts, casting a pall of doubt and uncertainty. But even as it haunts us, we must remember that it is a part of us. We must learn to accept its presence, and to use it to our advantage. For fear is not always a curse, it is a guide that shows us where we must grow stronger. It is a companion that walks with us through the dark night, illuminating the path ahead. By embracing our fears, we find the courage to face them, and to overcome them. We find the strength to live fully, to love fiercely, and to pursue our dreams with abandon.

Controls :

• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

Specter of Fears by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2023

metadata.name: k3rnel #143
metadata.description:
Self-organizing future-jazz geometry for like-minded pixel based neighbourhoods. 


********
Glossary
********

'Self-organization' → the process by which individuals organize their communal behaviour to create global order by interactions amongst themselves rather than through external intervention or instruction.

'Future-jazz-geometry' → propulsive syncopated visual rhythms, polyphonic ensemble playing, varying degrees of improvisation, and often deliberate distortions of pitch and timbre.

'Like-minded' → sharing the same opinions, ideas, or interests. 

'Pixel' → the smallest addressable element in an all points addressable display device; so it is the smallest controllable element of a picture represented on the screen.

'Neighbourhood' → a spatial unit, in which face-to-face social interactions occur.

Touch to listen, go fullscreen

metadata.description:

Is it the end?

-

[ARROW UP] - Ticket Up.
[ARROW DOWN] - Ticket Down.

[S] - Render a 40 frames gif.
[D] - Render a 60 frames gif.
 
[Z] - Save a printscreen of canvas.
[X] - Up/Down ballons.
[C] - Open/Close blueprint.

metadata.name: Subdivisions #207
metadata.description:
As an artist with a background in engineering, I have always been a fan of technical drawings.
Architectural sketches and renderings fascinate me with their ability to visualize the conceptual.

I create generative art for the same reason - to reveal the beauty in an algorithm.

This project represents the division of space using techniques that, for me, call to mind sitting
at a drafting table, straight edge in hand, imagining what might be possible.

You can export a high resolution PNG (5000x5000) by pressing the 'e' key.

Twitter: @jeffpalmer
https://jpalmer.dev

metadata.name: LAND++ #5
metadata.description:
NOTE：
This work 《LAND++》 is a free mint work for collectors who own 《LAND》.
《LAND》 had a bug in it due to an error on my part, which caused the image to be blurred like an ink painting when displayed in Live View mode.
(This is a problem of misconfiguration of pixelDensity, and this problem can be avoided by setting the browser zoom size to 50% or less.)

This bug has been fixed in《LAND++》.
Thank you again to the collectors.

-----------------------------------------

It has been over a year since I released 《MOUNTAINS》 in 2023. In this work, while utilizing some of the same algorithms as 《MOUNTAINS》, we draw various landscapes with a simple code of less than 200 lines. By applying FLUX processing to geometric forms, we give a certain kind of gravity to the shapes.
Fertile lands, rugged terrains, desolate fields, and scorched earth（焼け野原） are generated.

1920×1080 px
p5js

metadata.name: CA Panico #197
metadata.description:
Third chapter of the trilogy dedicated to Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.
 
Compared to CA Vista and CA Monti, CA Panico aims to further abstract the concept of landscape using CA rules in a more massive way.

The great variety of CA rules that controls the coloring and textures, noise influence, division into quadrants, chance of having glitches and outages all combined with 25 palettes and 5 different formats means that the outputs will be very varied and peculiar.

Press 'S' to download, you can zoom downloaded output to enjoy all the details.
